caption.body: Before the age of instant updates and Google Maps, good old-fashioned paper flyers kept passengers updated on airline and airport changes. In 1982, Pacific Southwest Airlines (PSA) moved terminals at SFO from Pier D in the Central Terminal (now Terminal 2) to Pier E in the South Terminal (now Terminal 1). Do you remember flying PSA out of SFO? #SFOHistory #ThrowbackThursday  Pacific Southwest Airlines (PSA) traveler information, San Francisco International Airport (SFO) 1982 SFO Museum Collection Gift of the William Hough Collection 2007.011.399  2007.011.398
